A N A C T
RELATING TO TAXATION -- PROPERTY SUBJECT TO TAXATION
Introduced By: Representatives Santucci, and Costantino
Date Introduced: June 06, 2025
Referred To: House Municipal Government & Housing
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 44-3 of the General Laws entitled "Property Subject to Taxation" is
2 hereby amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 44-3-28.1. Smithfield -- Exemption for people with paraplegia.
4 The town council of the town of Smithfield may, by ordinance, provide for a tax credit on
5 real property situated in the town, owned and occupied by any person with paraplegia and who by
6 reason of the paraplegic disability requires “specially adapted housing”. For the purposes of this
7 section, “specially adapted housing” means real property which has been specifically altered and/or
8 changed in some way in order to meet the needs of a person or persons with a paraplegic disability
9 who reside at the property.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
